The '''Guadalcanal white-eye''' ('''''Zosterops oblitus''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Zosteropidae]]. It is found on [[Guadalcanal]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is in [[subtropical]] or [[tropical]] moist [[montane forest]]s. The Guadalcanal white-eye was formerly considered a subspecies of the [[grey-throated white-eye]] (''Zosterops fuscicapilla'').<ref>{{Cite web|title=Species Updates – IOC World Bird List|url=https://www.worldbirdnames.org/new/updates/species-updates/|access-date=2021-05-28|language=en-US}}</ref>

